   Ad Notes. . . .
                                                                                                       

   AD SPENDING: Restaurants and fast-food chains increased TV
ad spending 11% in 1989 over the year before, to $1.5
billion, according to the Television Bureau of Advertising.
McDonald's was the largest spender, at $412 million, up 7%
from 1988; Burger King came in second, spending $161.6
million, up 8%; and Kentucky Fried Chicken, the third-largest
TV advertiser, spent $115.7 million, up 17% from 1988.
                                                                                                       

